{
  "text": "The fit results are a = (28.5 \u00b1 1.0)% \u00b7 GeV 1/2 and b = (3.5 \u00b1 0.1) %. The constant term is consistent with that obtained in a previous beam test while the stochastic term is somewhat improved over the previous result [CITATION_1] . The statistical uncertainties are small; the quoted uncertainties are dominated by systematics associated with the choice of selection criteria, cylinder cluster radius, and fitting procedures.",
